==English==
===Pronunciation===
*[[IPA]]: /ˈfɛ̙.ɹi/
*Other 1: (fâʹrē)
*Other 2: FAI(R)-ree
*{{audio|en-us-ferry.ogg|Audio (US)}}
**Homophones: [[fairy]]

===Etymology===
ult. from Old Norse ''[[ferja]]'', via Middle English

===Noun===
'''ferry''' ([[ferries]])

#A ship used to transport people, smaller vehicles and goods from one port to another, usually on a regular schedule

